## Additional Terms and Conditions

### API Usage
This software integrates with third-party APIs including but not limited to:
- Perplexity AI API
- OpenAI API (optional)

Users are responsible for:
- Obtaining their own API keys from respective providers
- Complying with the terms of service of these third-party APIs
- Managing their own API usage limits and costs

### Data Privacy
- This software processes insurance policy documents and user queries
- Users are responsible for ensuring they have proper authorization to process any documents
- The software does not store or transmit user data to unauthorized third parties
- Users should review and comply with applicable data protection regulations

### Disclaimer
This software is provided for educational and research purposes. Users should:
- Verify the accuracy of AI-generated responses independently
- Not rely solely on this software for critical insurance decisions
- Consult with qualified professionals for important policy matters
- Test thoroughly in their specific use case before production deployment

### Contributing
Contributions are welcome! Please:
- Fork the repository
- Create a feature branch
- Make your changes
- Add tests for new functionality
- Submit a pull request

### Support
For support, questions, or issues:
- Check the README.md file for documentation
- Review the test suite for usage examples
- Open an issue on the project repository

